The feeding of an obese child: don't eat breakfast and take charcuterie for dinner
More than one third of children between the ages of 9 and 13 have overweight problems, 9% of schoolchildren have overweight above average and 5% are obese.
As current research shows, obese children come from families who have a unhealthy lifestyle.
This shows again how important is the environment in which the human being and the models around it are.
For example, 50% more often than in families of children with normal weight are found in obese children's tables.
19% of the obese had fries at dinner according to the investigation conducted with an awareness action "obesity is not a coincidence"
In the families of the small big sports is also not a habit, which is now the case of most schoolchildren today - only 15% answered that at least once a week the parents found the time for active movement.
Survey of 900 children
The survey took place during the last school year and attended 900 primary school students in Czech Republic.
It was the second edition of "Obesity is not an accident", action supported by the General Health Insurance and Unilever society.
Since the beginning, more than 12000 students from 6th to 3rd enrolled in this project.
One of the determining factors that cause a dramatic increase in the number of children in overweight, or even obese, is the absence, of a proper diet and not enough physical exercise.
"Only half of the children questioned indicate, for example, eating 5 times a day breakfast in case - lunch - taste - dinner, which is a basic principle of good food," says one of the results of the survey.
No breakfast and charcuterie at dinner
Specialists draw attention to the fact that to have healthy development you need some basic details such as a family breakfast at the same time.
In Czech Republic, only 23% of the pupils' families eat at the same time.
In most families each takes his own breakfast.
And the worst thing that's ever been noticed is that a tenth of the population doesn't have breakfast at all.
Breakfast is, however, the basis of a good daily diet.
The questionnaire showed that in families of obese children, unhealthy fries are more often consumed.
Almost every student - not to mention weight - drinks sugar every day (70%).
More than 40% of the children questioned do sports regularly, but for parents it is half, only 15%.
Prepare your diet.
Another part of the survey allowed selected children (204 boys and 172 girls from 13 schools) to prepare their own food on the basis of opportunities offered according to their own taste and personal opinion.
"Czech children's preferences between 12 and 15 years of age are far from ideal for healthy food."
Among their favorite dishes are a lot of cakes, meats and sugars.
"The most alarming is, in particular, a great preference for sugared lemonades", is indicated in the results of the survey.
For lunch it's pasta that took the first place right in front of white meat.
Children did not want any fertility and the preference for fish and vegetable meals was very low.
Head of Health
The survey also showed that children are ready to change their habits from the moment they receive ad hoc information.
"In the course of a review of a group of survey participants who completed the questionnaire after the awareness session " Obesity is not an accident," a well-resolved desire to go to a healthy diet," indicates the results of the survey.
For example, the most striking was for sugary lemonades because children began to give preference to drinking water.
Children most often checked the questionnaire for white meat and fish as the main dish and would reduce sweet dishes and "knedlike" (Czech specialty of breadmeal or potatoes).
