The need for speed The Run fights across America.
By Way of Review
Originally, a race without problems is transformed because of a set of stupid mistakes of people who have nothing to do with a routine morning shift at work.
This fills to a certain extent the ambition of each but it serves no purpose if no one wants to do anything more.
The new section entitled The Run produced great expectations before its release.
He promised to take a new direction with the already old Need for Speed race series and to come out some sort of game from the playable parts that would not just count on points.
So we were curious about how the passages added in which the main hero came out of his car and did what he wanted.
As already in the NFS series, the result is completely different from what was expected.
These are potentially arcade racing games, but the whole shoots down because of some unnecessary mistakes that have existed for several years.
These are not really mistakes, but rather the expression of an incomprehensible pheneantisia on the part of the developers.
The adventure begins very well.
You are caught in the adventure of which the main hero Jack has character problems and to settle them gets involved in illegal races across America.
You are sitting behind the wheel on the west coast in San Francisco and your mission is to arrive first in New York.
The idea has interesting elements.
The route is divided into ten stages and then into more than 50 races.
The result is that each race takes place on another route and the stages planned in different environments that are quite distinct from each other and are interesting.
The player does not have the feeling that the game offers him something identical.
Some environments are quite beautiful overcrowding even though the graphic technical level is the same as the previous series.
Finally, it's not the end of the world.
But driving through the desert, in autumn landscapes or in high snowy mountains is very pleasant visually.
The tests are more time-consuming with an atypical element.
For example in the desert you find yourself in a sandstorm that significantly reduces your visibility.
Then in the mountains you must be careful that an avalanche does not fall on you.
Next to that, the different races are well arranged behind each other.
There is only a small number of them, but that is enough.
There are moments you try to exceed the number of opponents (like in a classic race) then run against the watch ( classic duel with the timer) and then wait for another duel with an opponent.
From time to time you also have the police that enter the game and try to make your situation difficult.
The novelty is the out-of-vehicle passages.
Rather, it's an interactive animation when most of the time Jack runs away from someone and you have to help him by tapping on the right button at the right time.
Nothing complicated.
What is surprising is that there are fewer moments of this kind than what you expect (to be concrete there are only three).
The result is as well because this element is not likely to interfere and places itself, in the context described above, in the elements that enhance the game.
The driving model is in the tradition of previous games.
Which means that at present there is nothing extraordinary but it cannot be said to be negative.
As far as realistic simulation is concerned, you should go and see elsewhere.
But although one can find better in the competition the driving model goes very well with the type of racing design.
So everything's okay.
Problems begin to appear after some time.
Unlike the driving model, collisions are not yet up to date.
We do not expect complicated deformation and collisions from this game, but when you don't have, during a collision with any object, the slightest idea of how your car behaves, it is therefore not completely good.
During tight overshoots you sometimes touch each other slightly but otherwise your car leaves in crazy shells.
Or they're in socks.
Thanks to the restarting system this is not really a problem but it really annoys you.
The restart is done in such a way that when you broke your face or you went out in the decor the game brings you back at the last point on the itinerary.
But you only have 5 restarts.
When you have used the 5 restarts you have to start the game from the beginning.
So it's more a tool, if something doesn't happen as it should be, than something you can really count on.
Sometimes restarts do not help and the solution needs to be found by recalling the part of the route in question.
The great hyc of this game is that the same actions are found in the same places.
For example, there are some turns that need to be passed in a certain way, otherwise that does not happen.
Otherwise you meet at a given location of "civil" vehicles always in the same configuration as you arrive first, fifth, 5 seconds in advance or one minute in delay.
What makes you angry are the situations when you see the opponent easily passing between two cars coming in the opposite direction and when you arrive, you have to either stand aside and turn them around or brake them.
It's the same if you go ahead of him because it's "calculated" so that for the given situation it always happens close to your nose.
Opponents still have other advantages.
Throughout the game, you, you arrive in some places, again without worrying about the time, and you always have the same opponent that precedes you in the same place.
This gets the most annoying at the end of the game when you ride on a long bridge in the opposite direction.
The opponent must at all costs pass before you.
When it passes before you it hides the view of other vehicles in the reverse and you collide a lot of times.
We can understand that the purpose of this game is to do something captivating and full of Adredalin, but it is clear that you are bored quickly.
And it's bad because through a simple driving model the game is interesting and places with so much action that you don't have time to follow everything that's going on.
And it's equal if it's because of the concept of 50 unique routes, that the order of the races is such that there's no chance of getting bored or anything else.
The original idea is the change of car during the races.
You need to be careful about petrol pumps on the routes because you can change cars however most of the time the one you have enough.
The cars are divided into three categories.
Sports cars are ideal for cities, large U.S. bicycles for straight highways and super sports cars around exotic roads on very technical routes, for example, on lace roads in the mountains.
And the way of challenges, which are races in particular places that you know of adventure, goes very well with the main regime of history.
You receive not only medals but also points of experience that add to your profile that are common to challenges and adventure.
When you have reached the highest level of driver, different objects begin to unfold:
This one connects online with the Autolog function that compares your results with those of other players and provides you with other functions in the community.
One of the most difficult to understand is the situation of the last race of adventure.
You arrive with your car in the tunnel of the metro (sa-like) where you drive in the darkness on the tracks (sa-like).
Your speed indicator tells you between 150 and 200 km/h (priority) and behind you comes a metro branch that sends you the car directly to the hardware.
At the writing we had a discussion for a few days whether someone really thought about the creation of this game or whether the authors really take us for fools.
The technical part of the game is not extra, but the visual part is generally pleasant and in some cases really great.
What is embarrassing is that in more extreme situations, imaging does not hold the level and in some cases tragically.
This mainly concerns accidents with a large number of participants when a fluid imaging is no longer useful to you.
The sound part is good and the track is in choice.
In order to please the greatest number and especially the young audience a new soundtrack was created in the style "I mix everything", but one can expect that no one will buy the game for music.
General Impression of Need for Speed: The Run is therefore really confused.
If the game did not have these stupid mistakes, we could say without fear that it is the best production of NFS in recent years.
But this game gives the impression that it's not over.
Fun is really good, but prepare yourself for the fact that the faults hit you in the eyes with the strength of an aerodrome reflector.
The Velvet Students in concert with the choirs of Charles University
The Festival Festival Festival Academica for the third time offers festivals that connect the International Student Day with the anniversary of the Velvet Revolution with a musical part.
During the festival there are 20 choirs of high schools and secondary classes.
The festival was set up in two concerts organized on 17 November.
"Charles University has an important part in this festival."
"There is the Choeur of the Faculty of Pedagogy and Humanities in the festival committee sits the Vaclav Hampl Rector," says the leader of the organizing team Jakub Calou.
The key to the festival is the Choeur des lycées and secondary classes concert, which takes place with free entry on 17 November from 2 p.m. on the space located in front of the National Technical Library in Dejvice.
In the program there is the composition of the well-known Czech jazzman Karel Ruzicka, Celebration Jazz Mass.
In the evening the concert "Students of Velours" takes place in the premises of the National House in Vinohrady, during which the choirs of the higher schools occur, as well as that of Charles University.
The aim of the Festival Academy is not only to celebrate the International Day of Students with dignity and recall the 22nd anniversary of the Velvet Revolution, but also to present to the public a music of the highest level and to develop the creative cooperation of young people.
The main organizer is the Union of Czech Cherries in cooperation with the Jan Kepler High School.
All the action is placed under the aegis of Bohuslav Svoboda, Mayor of Prague and Vaclav Hampl, Rector of Charles University.
The festival takes place from 16 to 20 November in Prague and Pardubice.
The program also offers high-level concerts, music meetings, student learning and other activities.
The interested parties will find all information on the Internet pages of the festival www.festaacademica.cz.
