Thus was the work of the person of Cali who identified the body of Alfonso Cano
A Cali dactyloscope has passed to history as the man who confirmed the death of "Alfonso Cano'.
The work of these staff members is crucial.
On November 4th, a California CTI dactyloscope passed on to history as the person who confirmed the identity of the chief of the Farcs: "Alfonso Cano", confronting his fingerprints.
Seven dactyloscopes working in the local offices of the ITC this week were the "availability" tour of Eliazar González, a man from Puerto Tejada who has worked in the field of judicial investigation for 21 years.
At the beginning of his career, González worked in the municipalities of Chocó, where many times he had to spend more than five days in the forest to reach the place where the bodies were to be identified.
In 2000, he moved to the capital city of Valle and after taking appropriate courses, he specialized in dactyloscopy, which is the study of friction skin, i.e. palms and feet.
During the week of the operation against alias Alfonso Cano, Eliasar was advised to take clothes with him for at least three days.
Something very big was waiting for him.
Friday night he left for Cauca in a Palmira helicopter.
He knew that he had to identify two bodies and that one of them was suspected to be the man who was leading the oldest guerrilla in the world, so he was asked to take the card with the ten fingerprints of Guillermo León Sáenz (his real name).
But when he arrived with the investigation team at the location of the body, he did not recognize it by his physical appearance, because this one was very different from the one he had seen in the media.
He had no beard, he was dressed like a peasant in the area, with no glasses and much thinner.
But fingerprints don't lie.
Accompanied by a galtonian magnifying glass, ink, picker and lantern, Eliazar compared the fingerprints of the body with those of the map.
His eye did not deceive him: it was "Alfonso Cano".
That same night, the man from Puerto Tejada was responsible for confirming to the Minister of Defense, Juan Carlos Pinzón that yes, he was the Supreme Chief of the Farcs.
In search of the fingerprint
For a Dactyloscope from Sijín de Cali the recognition that President Juan Manuel Santos made to Eliazar González at a press conference for the operation against "Cano", is very significant.
A lot of people don't know our work.
Dactyloscopy is an accurate science, without any margin of error, which can be crucial in solving crimes.
In addition to identifying the bodies, the dactyloscopes support investigations into crimes such as theft and murder and confirm the identity of the captured persons.
When captured, many offenders present false identity cards or do not have documents.
We take their fingerprints and search them in the database.
The researcher said that in a case of theft he had to remove part of a wall from a house, because in this place the thief had supported his hand to bring out a safe full of jewelry and money.
"The walls are difficult because they are not adequate surfaces to draw a fingerprint of them, but in this case we have been able to get the footprint from all hands and identify the offender who had participated in various flights," he recalls.
Fingerprints may also discard or confirm suspects in homicide cases.
We recently found a dead man, with bottles of drink around him.
Through the investigation, it was determined that a parent may be a suspect of the crime and indeed a mark on the bottle coincided.
Even if it does not guarantee that he is the killer, it puts him on the scene of the crime.
One ITC dactyloscope explained that "digital fingerprints of objects with chemical or physical reagents" are extracted.
When they appear, a picker or strip is used to remove them.
Subsequently, fingerprints are sent to Asif, the database of the decliners, or to the National Civil Registry.
"The problem is that there are still many Colombians without papers," said the ITC expert.
He explained that everything is not how we show it in the CSI television program.
Like everything that shines isn't gold, everything that you touch doesn't become forced into a footprint.
However, it can be used if the necessary confrontation is achieved.
