In Chernobyl, the design of the reactor and unforgivable human faults caused the drama.
In Fukushima, some seem to forget that the accident results from two natural disasters of an unprecedented magnitude that have caused the deaths of tens of thousands.
The nuclear industry will learn from this accident, as it had done for the two previous ones.
